annotation.TEXT: Oh, noes. I missed a star coin. Whatever shall I do? Fear not, as the upward currents are not as effective as the other directional currents!
Whoops! I meant to grab that shell (which I should've switched to the cape to do). I hope I didn't need that shell for anything important...

However, I have no idea what's up ahead, and I wouldn't want the silver P-switch to take away a Banzai Bill that I'm supposed to stomp on or something like that, so I'll just wait here until its effect ends.
There's a bunch of coins in triangle shapes here.
Yiyiyiyi! Yeah, I knew I'd be able to get through that without ducking.
No, it looks like the best I can do is match its force. Even the turbo fire button can't actually overpower it.
50-star goal tape hits: 1
Ooh, this might be troublesome, since the downward currents are more effective than the upward ones. But, with this P-switch...

Also, if I ever do encounter Yoshi in this hack, I will be sure to try doing that sprite overloading thing in the bonus game. (But I'm guessing that one of the power ups would simply disappear and that's all.)
Whoa, big bullet that I was lucky to land on.
Goal tape average so far: 160 / 4 = 40 stars each.
Ooh, I wonder how tricky this setup would be without the P-switch? Probably not very tricky, actually.
Oh, heck, yeah! Well, I certainly proved that I didn't need that timed lift alright! And this also got me a 3♥P! (Also, it's funny how the "Hurry Up!" sound effect occurred right at that moment.)
...I could try out 9-1 next.
...I may not have to deal with those currents down there at all!
Oh, man. This looks tricky...
Argh!!! I was a split-second too late to get in there for that last star coin... I'll have to try for the star coins again next time.
Goal tape average so far: 200 / 5 = 40 stars each.
Or...
Since I can't fly, I've gotta stop this winged ? block in the right spot to allow me to reach the block above.
Okay, so we start off with timed lifts, and a feather falling from the sky, which I think I'll take. Oh, and that's neat how the number's circle on the lift becomes red when it's on the number "1".
To be continued...
Also, star made out of brown blocks.
Umm... I think I was supposed to use that timed lift to reach the goal tape. But, I've got a cape, so who needs that lift?
BGM: Super Mario Galaxy - Rosalina's Observatory
Bah, I only got 30. Now I'll need to get another 50 in order to bring my average back up to 40 again...
...Eh, what? I was expecting something like the usual "Yellow Switch Palace" there, but instead there's a warp star that's labelled "W9"?
Well, let's take a look, I guess...
Not quite, but my shell is still in play!
Okay, my hypothesis: The upward force of the current can't completely counteract my descending speed, and if I'm not completely overlapping the current, its effect on me is reduced.

Hello, and welcome back to Super Marina World! Last time, I had a choice between going to the water level in the middle (1-3), or going to the secret red level in the upper-left (1-A). And, I let you guys vote on this one, so let's take a look at those voting results...
O-w-w-w-w... S-t-u-p-i-d... e-v-i-l... n-i-n-j-a... t-u-r-t-l-e...
Oh, what's this? Are we going to be dealing with currents now?
Oh, right. I've actually gotta paddle a little bit for the upward current to do its job.
So far nothing ridiculously tricky yet... Maybe a few mildly tricky things for those without attack-enabled power ups...
Ha! I thought that ledge seemed suspicious!
Oh, man. The trickiness level has definitely increased here!
I guess I'll do 1-3 next, since it wouldn't be right to go straight into the castle without holding a vote for it first.
Well, there's my 1♥P combo, even though I only got one, but it still counts.
Okay, and now that I'm past that part that Windows Movie Maker gave me a lot of grief with, let's see if I can do this P-switch run fast enough to reach the last star coin this time!
Oh, man. This game's making me do tricky moves like this in world 1?
BGM: Kirby's Return to Dreamland - Super Ability
Oh, man. If a world 1 level (even if it's a secret level) is going to get trickier than the original game's Valley of Bowser 3, I wonder how nasty the later worlds will be in terms of difficulty...
Oh, maybe I should check these pipes. Although... I'm probably not even expected to be able to land on them in the first place, so they mostly likely wouldn't be exit-enabled.
Yeah, that picture was included with this hack, so I figured I'd show it off here. (And the music that I used there was a piece of Tetris Attack's Yoshi's theme.)
Okay, I managed to roast Rip Van Fish without letting it smack me. Now, it should be a simple task to get that star coin, right?
But... Which level should I play next? I don't want this to be just a one-level episode...
I don't know about the idea of making "cape-nerfing" patches STANDARD... I mean, of course, have them as an option, but hackers shouldn't be forced to nerf cape flight.
...Um, yeah, after doing seven laps...
Hmm... I still think I want to keep my cape in reserve.
Well, that's interesting. This must be like the special world or something. However, I think I'm going to hold off on entering world 9-1 for the moment.
Yes, I made it this time, and there's a timed lift up here, which leads to...
Huh, a just-off-screen ceiling. I'd better keep that in mind.
Well, that was a long corridor with not much in it. (It probably would've been more interesting if I was fleeing from pursuing RVFs, but since I cooked them all...)

Okay, this opened a path straight to the castle, which is labelled "1-5". Of course, I'm not going there quite yet. For one thing, I've still gotta find the secret exit (and get all of the star coins) in 1-A!
Umm... That's weird. This seems like an upward-moving current, but I'm still somehow able to move downwards through it...
Oh, and it's obvious that I've gotta use the blue P-switch now!
Oh, I probably could've gotten a 1-up combo with those parakoopas if I had thought about it. Well, maybe I can do that on my second trip through this level, since this is a red level.
Alright, I got it this time! Oh, but I thought I saw something else up there...? Hmm... Maybe I can shell jump up...
Okay, there's a downward-moving current there. Can I swim against it?
And, there you have it. 1-A won, so that's where I'm going next!
Heck, yeah. Goin' for a swim. Hmm... I think I'll want to switch to fireballs here. They have better range than the cape.
Goal tape average so far: 230 / 6 = 38.333 stars each.
Whoa, big bullet.
So, viewers, vote for either 1-4, 1-5, or 9-1, and then, using the power of those votes, we'll find out which level I'll begin the next episode with next time!
Um, whoops! I'm surprised that sudden block-cloning attempt worked on the first try!
Time to murder some RVFs!
And, unsurprisingly, this unlocks 1-4. So, where should I head next?
Oh, man. Now we've got a current that's not underwater, and this one's more effective at pushing me upwards!
Whoo-hoo!
Wheeee!!!
Bonus game average so far: 16 / 2 = 8 1-ups each.
...what I assume is the secret exit! Ooh, and I got exactly enough stars for a bonus game!
I could go to 1-4 of course, or go straight to the castle, 1-5...
